# Card-audit puzzle (mtg-948 Part B) backing CLOSED issue mtg-401
# (Card Compatibility: Serra Angel).
#
# Aspects exercised:
#   1. K:Flying — a 4/4 flier can only be blocked by creatures with flying or
#      reach (CR 702.9). P1's only creature is a ground Grizzly Bears, which
#      CANNOT block Serra Angel, so all 4 combat damage gets through.
#   2. K:Vigilance — Serra Angel does not tap to attack (CR 702.21), so it
#      stays untapped and available to block on the crackback.
#   3. Parses as a 4/4 Angel for {3}{W}{W}.
#
# P0 attacks each turn with the flying, vigilant Serra Angel; P1 at 8 life
# cannot block the flier and dies within two swings.
#
# HOW TO RUN / VERIFY interactively:
#   mtg tui --start-state test_puzzles/audit_serra_angel_flying_vigilance.pzl \
#       --p1 heuristic --p2 heuristic --seed 42 -v 2 --no-color-logs
# The log shows Serra Angel dealing 4 unblocked flying damage per turn and
# remaining untapped (vigilance) between attacks.

[metadata]
Name:Serra Angel flying + vigilance beats a ground blocker (audit mtg-401)
Goal:Win
Turns:4
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 attacks with a 4/4 flying, vigilant Serra Angel. P1's only creature is a ground Grizzly Bears, which cannot block the flier (CR 702.9), so 4 damage connects each turn; P1 at 8 life dies in two swings. Vigilance keeps Serra Angel untapped between attacks (CR 702.21). Assertions confirm P0 wins, P1 takes lethal, and Serra Angel survives on P0's battlefield.

[state]
turn=2
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=
p0library=Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains
p0graveyard=
p0battlefield=Serra Angel; Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains
p0exile=

p1life=8
p1hand=
p1library=Forest; Forest; Forest; Forest; Forest
p1graveyard=
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears; Forest; Forest
p1exile=

[assertions]
# P0 wins: the flier P1 cannot block carries the game.
game won
# P1 takes lethal flying damage (started at 8; ends at 0 or below).
opponent life le 0
# Serra Angel is still on P0's battlefield at game end (it was unblockable, so
# it never died); P0 keeps at least one permanent.
battlefield count ge 1
